Rating: 3
This is a sneaky one. When I was tasting throughout (to test the rice), the taste of the rosemary was way too strong, and I thought it was going to be a bust. But after the final addition of broth, it was excellent. I didn't add procini, and I cut the amount of rosemary slightly (I like, but do not love rosemary), but otherwise stayed true. Very good. Ignore the silly people who are offended by purple risotto; it's not really unusual to use red wine in risotto.

