Rating: 3
This dish was a nice treat. We used bacon instead of pancetta. However, we were a little dissapointed that there wasn't more of a bacon flavor. Overall, the taste was a little bland considering all the yummy things that went into it. I wonder if it was because there was so much chicken stock compared to 1 tbsp of sage and rosemary? I will try this dish again, but will try cutting the amount of rice in half (way too much for just 2 people) but keeping the rest of the goodies at the same amount. Might even try cooking the bacon separatly and adding at the end to preserve some of the bacon flavor instead of bacon soaked in chicken stock. Not really sure if our dissapointment was because we used bacon instead of pancetta. Really enjoyed the red wine flavor. Used a nice merlot. Not one of my favorite risottos, but definately still worth making.

Rating: 3
I had some portabellas on hand, which I chopped and used instead of cremini. Regular bacon works fine if no pancetta available. Whoever used a 40 dollar bottle of wine in this recipe is crazy--what a ridiculous waste--using a basic dry red table wine (3-7 dollars) worked fine and was delicious. (I make risotto about once a week and believe me, the quality of the wine does little to the final flavor of the risotto--the quality of the broth, however, has a great deal to do with it, I always use homemade chicken broth.) The rosemary and sage worked beautifully together. It was an easy comfort food to make.

